6. The system of claim 3 wherein the neutral beam injection system comprises:
a plasma formation box which is a separate chamber from said reactor chamber and is configured to receive said fusion fuel and ionize said fusion fuel to form a source plasma;
an ion extraction grid for continuously extracting a plurality of desired ions from said source plasma where the extracted ions form an ion beam;
an ion acceleration grid where the ion beam is accelerated through a potential gradient of an electric field and where the energy of the resulting ion beam is a function of said gradient;
a charge exchange box where the ion beam is neutralized through the charge exchange process with a neutralizing gas to form the neutral beam;
wherein the neutral beam is aimed at the core of the plasma located in said reactor chamber and the neutral beam is caused to flow towards the core such that fuel is provided for the fusion process.

16. The method according to claim 11 wherein the injection of the fusion fuel includes:
injecting the fusion fuel into a plasma formation box;
ionizing the fusion fuel in the plasma formation box whereby a plasma source is formed;
extracting a plurality of desired ions, by an ion extraction grid, from the plasma source, where the extracted ions form an ion beam;
accelerating, by an ion acceleration grid, the ion beam through the potential gradient of an electric field, where the energy of the resulting ion beam is function of said gradient;
directing the resulting ion beam into a charge exchange box;
injecting a neutralizing gas into the charge exchange box and neutralizing the ion beam, whereby a neutral beam is formed; and
injecting the neutral beam toward a core of the plasma located in said reactor chamber, such that fuel is provided for the fusion process.
